                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2501</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PFC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-15T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 16, 9.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1188. Communicated your 1157<note n="1" xml:id="d263fn1">See No. 2790 to the
                        Ambassador in Germany, March 9, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_202">p. 202</ref>.</note> to Ministry of Foreign Affairs
                    to-day as instructed. <persName corresp="#p_BVRSB1">Baron Burian</persName> was
                    impressed with clearness of your statement and said that your <hi rend="italic"
                        >bona fides</hi> could not be questioned. He remarked that the incident
                    involved no question of veracity, but had been a case of misunderstanding.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
